ht glided over the asphalt and the same good-natured taxi that had taken Günther away somewhere, softly pulled in alongside the sidewalk. 'Another one?' laughed the driver. 'They could have gone together.' 'But where?' Karl asked Kurt sleepily. 'There must be an address of some kind — let's look in his pockets...' the latter answered vaguely. Swaying and involuntarily nodding, they bent over the motionless man and the fact that his overcoat was unbuttoned facilitated their further exploration